The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, gave a press briefing on July 17, 2013. He discussed the Affordable Care Act, also known as Obamacare, and the benefits it provides to Americans. Carney mentioned that 8.5 million consumers would be receiving half a billion dollars in rebates that summer. He also highlighted that New York State announced a reduction in health insurance plan rates, with the cost for the most comprehensive plans being down by over 50 percent. Carney criticized the House of Representatives for voting to repeal the Affordable Care Act and explained that the law is providing enormous benefits to the American people. He also discussed other topics such as the Senate deal on nominees, the crisis in Syria, the Snowden case, the situation in Egypt, and the President's meeting with senators to discuss student loans.